  "text": "Our current approach is ideal for visualization of retinal endothelial molecules, since the structure of the eye provides a unique platform for light-based molecular imaging. The high sensitivity and specificity of the molecular imaging probes make them highly suitable for the detection of low-grade inflammation, as observed in DR. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Using this non-invasive approach, we demonstrated elevated ICAM-1 expression levels in the retinal vessels of T1D animals. This novel approach represents a great advancement that can be applied to humans.",
